latestPosts.caption:
The last few days have been nothing short of magical — I’ve never felt more accepted, more held, more seen by Shivji.
With a heart full of devotion, I’ve completed 5 out of the 12 Jyotirlings.

🕉️ Mahakaleshwar — where time dissolves and the Bhasma Aarti reminds you that everything, even the body,is made for  Shiva’s dance. Spent the whole time looking at him with all the love and my whole heart is full.

🕉️ Omkareshwar — nestled between river and rock, where I felt Shivji’s presence in every cell of my body, feeling chills while typing this as well. 

🌕 Baglamukhi Maa — the warrior goddess who silences chaos and grants unwavering inner strength,  and  removes all negativity, where maa loves the colour yellow and Sarsarwati ji and Lakshmi maa also sit by her. 

🌸 Harsiddhi Ma — ancient, radiant, and fierce, her temple pulses with Shakti and surrender— this is the temple where Sati Maas tongue fell. 

🥃 Kal Bhairav — where you offer liquor, but truly leave behind fear, pride, and pretense.
🚬 Vikrant Sarkar — the smoking deity who breaks every norm, reminding you that divinity isn’t always what you expect — it’s what you feel.
🕉️ Mahameshwar — a temple carved in stillness, holding stories in stone with ancient scriptures was just something else. 

Shivji’s love is unlike anything else — I feel it in every breath, every blessing, every beat of my being.
This journey has really caused a shift me.🧿🧿🧿🧿🧿🧿🧿🧿🧿🧿🧿🧿🩷🩷🩷🩷🩷🩷🩷🩷🩷🩷

#jyotirling #mahakaleshwar #bhasmaaarti #omkareshwar #shiv #baglamukhi #harsiddhi #kalbhairav #shivashakti #india #god #culture #ujjain #indore
